## Critical Issues Found

### 1. **Silent Error Handling in Task Managers**
Both `TaskManager` and `EisenhowerTaskManager` have critical issues with error handling:

**In TaskManager (<mcfile name="task_manager.dart" path="lib\\services\\task_manager.dart"></mcfile>):**
```dart
try {
  final file = File('${directory.path}/kanban_tasks.json');
  final contents = await file.readAsString();
  final List<dynamic> tasksJson = jsonDecode(contents);
  _tasks = tasksJson.map((json) => Task.fromJson(json)).toList();
  notifyListeners();
} catch (e) {
  // Silent failure - tasks could be lost!
  // print('Error loading tasks: $e');
}
```

**In EisenhowerTaskManager (<mcfile name="eisenhower_task_manager.dart" path="lib\\services\\eisenhower_task_manager.dart"></mcfile>):**
```dart
try {
  final file = File('${directory.path}/eisenhower_tasks.json');
  final contents = await file.readAsString();
  final List<dynamic> tasksJson = jsonDecode(contents);
  _tasks = tasksJson.map((json) => EisenhowerTask.fromJson(json)).toList();
  notifyListeners();
} catch (e) {
  // Silent failure - user data lost without notification!
  // print('Error loading tasks: $e');
}
```

**Impact:** Users lose all their tasks without any notification when file operations fail.
        
            
